And the scene where Wataru says he finds comfort in the outside Pokémon is one of my favorites as well! It gives me the sense of seeing his more innocent, childlike side. I only wish there were more moments where he could relax like that.
Wataru's comments that seem to show he's letting his guard down around us, the players, are also tied to this kind of thoughtfulness, aren't they?

I had never read the English version of the text, so it was very helpful! Wataru fully understands his position as both a Champion and a descendant of a prestigious lineage, and he is focused on acting in a way that is worthy of that. From my perspective, it even appears painfully so...
Thank you for reading my article and for your wonderful reply! I'm currently studying English, so please forgive me if there are any awkward parts in my writing.
